        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 10 at 10:56PM CDT by NWS Amarillo TX</headline>
        <description>At 1056 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Romero, or 14 miles northeast of Nara Visa, moving east at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Romero.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
